JSON Ignore, JSON Managed Reference, JSON Back Reference
1. @JsonIgnore Behavior

Completely ignores the field during serialization and deserialization.
If you try to pass values for the ignored field in a request (e.g., Postman),
→ It will throw an error because the field is not recognized for JSON processing.
If you use the ignored field inside methods of that class (like getters/setters or logic),
→ Postman may throw errors since the object might be null or missing during request handling.


2. @JsonManagedReference

Shows (serializes) the annotated object.
Used on the parent / owning side in bidirectional relationships.
It prevents infinite recursion by controlling which side should be displayed.


3. @JsonBackReference

Hides the annotated object from JSON output (serialization).
Used on the child / inverse side.
Even though it is hidden, the object is still functional internally and used by Hibernate/JPA.
Prevents infinite loop while still allowing the relationship to work.